display.shortDescription: A soup style shot with short soak followed by a high flow for course grounds.
display.description: A typical soup style profile which relies upon course grounds, low pressures, and high flow rates. The initial fill phase is intentionally a slow flow with a very low pressure cap on it, and is intended to soak the puck fully until you get a few drips in the cup.  You can adjust the duration of the soak and how many drips via the Soak Exit Weight variable. Adjust your grind size course enough to achieve at least 3-6mlps in the main extraction stage. Output ratios should typically be in the 1:3-1:5 range.
